JOHANNESBURG - The new SABC board hit its first crisis, with the sudden resignation of one of its members on Thursday.  Rachel Kalidass said the main reason for her leaving is the board's preferred CEO candidate, Alan Mukoki. WATCH: Maggs on Media : State of the SABC  The DA slammed the board's choice, saying Mukoki is unqualified for the position. Mukoki previously headed up the Land Bank and is the current CEO of the South African Chamber of Commerce and Industry. President Jacob Zuma finally appointed a permanent board to the embattled public broadcaster in October.  eNCA